Unique Passive: Instantly heal for 10% of all magical damage delt. This is 33% effective for area of effect damage. (same passive as Hextech Gunblade)

Unique Passive - Cleave: Basic attacks deal 5 (+10% AD)(+20%) Magic damage in a line behind the target (450 range) [procs as quickly as titanics](Cannot stack on-hit damage with Spellblade, Wit's End or Nashor's Tooth.)

Unique Active - Crescent: The next basic attack is enhanced, causing it to fire a bolt behind the target, that explodes upon reaching max range or hitting the next target dealing 10(+2*level)(+20% AD)(+25% AP). [550 range maybe?]

Tell me what you think in the comments bellow, might be a bit busted but those are things that can be fixed.

Edit: Noted unintended user would be Jax, idk if this would break him or not. Another one is probably Alistar and Blitzcrank, i think thresh has AP scalings too but i'm fairly sure this item wouldn't break them in a solo lane. Another one is Shaco who similar to Jax could build both AD and AP. 

Second Edit: Added Sejuanni and Mordekaiser 

Edit three: Lower the AP ratio's, they were too high, i was basing them off of ravenous hydra. 

Edit Four: The reason there is no AD in the final build is quite simple, i didn't want the item to be a go to for Jax or other Hybrid champions to abuse it. I did it on purpose. 

Edit five: Removed the Mana and added health regeneration(against my will.) Added fizz, cause i forgot you buddy.

Edit six: Added the AD back in and gave it a bit more so it's more gold efficient, changed the passive and actives to be different from Titanic Hydra and Ravenous Hydra.

Edit Seven: Removed the health regen.

